################################################################################
################################################################################
	README for the GRR Changes to i3c-tools
################################################################################
################################################################################

This started with https://github.com/vitor-soares-snps/i3c-tools.git,
but that project seems dead.  For GRR, clone
https://github.com/axxia/i3c-tools.git and switch to the grr branch.
Why the changes?  GRR has a very limited I3C controller.  The Linux
I3C core expects more from a controller!

Considering both points, 1) the upstream project seems to be dead and,
2) the GRR I3C controller will not be upstreamed due to the
limitations, this should just be used as an example.

So, here are the changes.

## 1 ##

Instead of meson, just use make.  make can handle cross-compiling, and
this is a simple build!

## 2 ##

As this branch is only intended to be used with GRR, see the README in
the I3C driver source for details.
